      <p class="pf-sub">Most Wirral homes with system or regular boilers rely on a hot water cylinder. These are the signs that replacement is due.</p>

      <div class="pf-signs" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Running out of hot water frequently</strong><p>The cylinder is undersized for current demand, or the immersion heater element has partially failed. A larger replacement cylinder or an upgrade to an unvented system resolves this permanently.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Cylinder is leaking</strong><p>A leaking cylinder must be replaced. A drip from a valve or fitting can sometimes be resolved without replacing the cylinder itself. We diagnose which on the visit.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Hot water takes more than 45 minutes to reheat</strong><p>A failing immersion heater element, corroded heat exchanger coil or faulty thermostat. We diagnose the cause before recommending replacement.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Cylinder is over 20 years old</strong><p>Most cylinders have a working life of 15 to 25 years. A Wirral cylinder over 20 years old is at increasing risk of failure. Proactive replacement avoids emergency water damage.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Poor hot water pressure throughout the property</strong><p>A vented system cannot deliver mains-pressure hot water. Upgrading to an unvented cylinder resolves this problem across all Wirral CH postcodes.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Banging or kettling from the cylinder or pipework</strong><p>Limescale build-up on the immersion element or heat exchanger, or air in the system. Often resolved with an element replacement before full cylinder replacement is needed.</p></div></div>
      </div>

